s services to retail and wholesale customers in the united states belgium and spain clearwire traces its roots to  when sierra technologies inc spun off certain assets to form a new company clearwire technologies inc in october  craig mccaw purchased clearwire technologies inc parent company clearwire holdings and moved the company headquarters to kirkland washington in  clearwire moved the company headquarters to bellevue washington a large percentage of clearwire shares were previously owned by a number of large companies including sprint nextel corporation now sprint corporation comcast corporation time warner cable inc bright house networks llc google inc and intel corporation sprint nextel was clearwires largest single shareholder owning a  combined stake and control of the company on july   sprint nextel completed acquiring the remaining shares it didnt already own becoming sole owner of clearwire corporation the day after on july   sprint nextel and softbank corp announced the completion of their merger where softbank invested  billion in sprint clearwire provided services to  markets in the united states covering  million potential subscribers sprint corporation owns rights to radio frequency spectrum in the  ghz range which provides service primarily using the g e mobile wimax standard clearwire also provides service to customers in  us cities using the motorola expedience d radio interface which the company refers to as preg clearwire was ranked as the fifth largest wireless provider in the us prior to being acquired with roughly  million subscribers who used the wimax network as of january  sprint ceased operations of the clearwire network on november   contents  history  complete acquisition by sprint nextel  networks  expedience ofdm  preg  wimax e  g  retail products and services  g mobile and fixed wireless  expedience fixed wireless  voip  wholesale products and services  criticism  see also  references  external links historyedit clearwire traces its roots to  when sierra technologies inc spun off certain assets to form a new company clearwire inc based in arlington texas clearwire technologies was formed by a number of investors including sierra ceo jim gero and edward rusty rose a former comanaging partner of the texas rangers clearwire technologies raised about us million from goldman sachs in conjunction with another client who held licenses for spectrum allocated to various educational institutions the former instructional television fixed service itfs band now known as ebs or educational broadband service after goldman provided the funds—which were supposed to be used to roll out the system in key markets across the us—they used a provision of the agreement to take control of the company hiring a new ceo leo j cyr who ousted the entire management team including clearwire ceo brian nerney while diluting the strength of the founders still on the board of directors a holding company controlled by craig mccaw flux llc acquired clearwire incs then parent company clearwire holdings in march  after assuming control mccaw installed executives from mccaw cellular in the key leadership positions at clearwire corp on june   mccaw purchased clearwire inc for an undisclosed amount and used its name and resources as well as technology developed by another mccawowned company nextnet wireless inc to launch his latest effort on october   intel corp teamed up with mccaw to develop and deploy a technology for portable wireless internet access the partnership included an investment by clearwire corp on march   bell canada invested  million us in seattlebased clearwire corpcitation needed clearwire grew from  customers in september  to more than  customers by may  clearwire claimed in september  that  of its markets had more than  penetration of households coveredcitation needed clearwire took a  million infusion of capital from intel and motorola in july  shortly after pulling its initial public offering clearwires equipment manufacturer nextnet wireless was sold to motorola as part of the exchange this investment by these two industry giants had been reported as an attempt to accelerate the development and deployment of wimax networks worldwide an unspecified source claims that att sold clearwire a slice of  ghz spectrum for about  million the spectrum covers markets in the southeast of the us and was formerly owned by bellsouth the spectrum solidifies clearwires position as the second largest holder of  ghz spectrum after sprint nextel att had to sell the spectrum as a condition of its merger with bellsouthcitation needed clearwire and sprint nextel announced a partnership in july  to accelerate deployment of wimax technology across the us the deal was to include a swap of spectrum and markets between the two companies as well as providing roaming capabilities for customers traveling between the companies networks the partnership was terminated at the end of  in  sprints new ceo dan hesse started serious discussions about forming a joint venture between the two companies in the hopes of bringing in outside funding from google intel and best buy on march   an anonymous source stated that sprint and clearwire may get as much as  billion from comcast and  million from time warner cable in financial backing clearwire filed for its initial public offering with the securities and exchange commission in may  the companys underwriters included merrill lynch morgan stanley and jpmorgan chase trading began march   under the ticker symbol clwr on the nasdaq clearwire offered  million shares at  a share and raised approximately us million before the sprint merger craig mccaw was the largest shareholder of the company with a majority of the shares on may   clearwire and sprint nextels wireless broadband unit xohm announced their intent to merge combining sprints g wimax network xohm with clearwires existing prewimax broadband network sprint owns  of the firm with exclearwire shareholders owning  — a consortium of comcast time warner cable intel google and bright house networks invested  billion and own the balance clearwire and the cable companies will buy g mobile broadband from sprint as mvnoscitation needed clearwiresprint nextel officially launched portland oregon as the first market using the new service clearwires g service was branded as clear except in those markets where the clearwire name has already been established and where clear service is not available clear g was available in  of the top  msas in the country covering  million people on march   clearwire named bill morrow as ceo succeeding benjamin wolff who became cochairman with craig mccaw morrow  stepped down as ceo of pacific gas  electric company morrow had previously held a number of senior positions at vodafone in april  a classaction lawsuit was filed against clearwire the suit was dismissed in april  but was appealed by the complainant the suit claimed that the companys actual internet connection speeds were slower than advertised and was sometimes unavailable on december   mccaw resigned as chairman of clearwire and was replaced by john w stanton on march   bill morrow resigned as ceo and was replaced by interim ceo john w stanton on august   clearwire promoted coo erik prusch to president and ceo named john stanton executive chairman clearwire stated that it may not honor a  million debt covenant due on december   in order to conserve cash however on december   the company announced that not only had it made that payment but it had made a new fouryear deal with sprint to receive funding for network buildout and investments valued at  billion complete acquisition by sprint nexteledit on october   it was announced that japanese telecommunications company softbank would purchase  of sprint nextel corporation for  billion this initially led to speculation that sprint would buyout clearwire but two well placed sources within sprint said that such a maneuver would not occur sprint however announced on october   that it acquired a majority interest in clearwire by buying a stake from clearwires founder which gave sprint a  ownership and control of clearwire on december   sprint announced that it entered into a definitive agreement to acquire the remaining stake in clearwire that it did not then own for  per share which equaled  billion over a period of approximately six months a bidding war with dish network for clearwire occurred ultimately resulting in sprint increasing its offer price for clearwire to  per share on july   clearwire announced that its stockholders approved the merger with sprint relatedly sprints stockholders approved the merger with softbank which closed on july   subsequently it planned to lay off about  of its employees clear announced that it would shut down on november   on november   clear service was terminated the wimax network was operated without clear customers until early march  because of a court order networksedit expedience ofdm  pregedit in  markets in the united states and certain markets in belgium clearwire provides a service it refers to as preg using a pointtomultipoint system from motorola called expedience part of the motowi family of products the service is considered true nonlineofsight nlos the service is not unique to clearwire several companies throughout the world use this same product line from motorola including inukshuk wireless partnership of canada beamspeed and commspeed of arizona accesstel of bangladesh and unitel of guatemala wimax e  gedit branded clear the company on january   unveiled portland oregon as its first g wimax wireless broadband market enabling consumers and businesses to access the internet wirelessly at broadband speeds since the portland launch the company has expanded its g network to  additional markets retail products and servicesedit g mobile and fixed wirelessedit logo used in the united states by clearwire to market g wireless internet services under the clear brand in the united states clearwire offers g fixed and mobile internet access under the clear brand in  cities clearwire claims an average download speed of  to  mbits with bursts over  mbits in january  clearwire started offering g wimax service in spain under the instanet brand discontinuing services based on motorola expedience technology clearwire provides service in spain in the    ghz frequency range logo used in spain by clearwire españa sa to market g wireless internet services under the instanet brand clearwire offers g wimax service in belgium under the clearwire brand logo used in belgium by clearwire belgium sprl to market g wireless internet services under the clearwire brand expedience fixed wirelessedit clearwire offers expedience based services in  markets in the united states and in certain markets in belgium customers can choose either the motorola expedience residential subscriber unit rsu or the motorola expedience pc card in both a pc card and expresscard the rsu incorporates automatic adaptive modulation for increased throughput and network capacity users are connected to the internet at indoor locations throughout the entire systems coverage area the unit functions as an ethernet bridge layer  device interfacing a standard ethernet over twisted pair connector the pc card incorporates the same automatic adaptive modulation for increased throughput and network capacity with the added portability of a laptop cardbus card clearwire formerly offered expedience based services in ireland  denmark until operations in those countries were purchased by imagine communications and erlo group respectively in january  clearwire discontinued services based on motorola expedience technology in spain in favor of instanet branded g wimax service voipedit clearwire also offers its own voice over ip service in some areas for an additional monthly fee clear wireless retail store in the borough of manhattan new york new york united states wholesale products and servicesedit sprint corporation clearwires parent company resells clearwires g network service as sprint g wimax in over  markets across the united states other clearwire investors comcast and time warner cable resell clearwire’s g mobile broadband service in a number of markets including new york city los angeles chicago philadelphia atlanta and portland among others bundled with their cable home phone and residential internet services on june   sprint nextel introduced the first commercially available g cellphone in the us the htc evo g the device combines clearwire’s g network with sprint’s g network and google’s android operating system creating a multimediaheavy device sprint hoped would set it apart from g smartphones like the apple iphone criticismedit in  clearwire drew criticism from phone operator vonage vonage claimed clearwire and other isps were blocking vonages services testing showed that contrary to vonages claims vonage calls were being connected over the clearwire network in september  clearwire introduced a dynamic network management system to punish users who consume disproportionate amounts of wireless data by limiting the user to about  kbits certain users claimed their terms of service were modified retroactively to reflect the new policy and clearwire itself has unofficially acknowledged this claim in the middle of  clearwire reached a settlement to provide partial refunds of termination fees and service credits for individuals who experienced throttling as part of their dynamic network management policy the settlement allows clear to continue throttling connections under certain circumstances as long as their advertising reflects this in september  clearwire in spain operating under the brand instanet cut off all of its services web and phone lines without prior notice spanish consumer associations are gathering evidence of possible overcharging on april   over a period of a few days clearwire cut off its clearwirenet email services in the united states on april   clearwire announced sprint will cease operations of the clear g wimax network and clearwire expedience network on november   sprint did not give clear subscribers any path to internet service by lte or other means through sprint see alsoedit sprint corporation google virgin mobile usa mobile broadband wireless broadband wireless internet service provider referencesedit  a b clearwire corporation  form k annual report pursuant to section  or d of the securities exchange act of  for the fiscal year ended december   commission file number  clearwire corporation united states securities and exchange commission retrieved    clearwire promotes erik prusch to president and ceo names john stanton executive chairman nasdaqclwr corporateclearwirecom archived from the original on  retrieved    q and fullyear  financial results httpnewsroomclearwirecomphoenixzhtmlcpirolnewsarticleidhighlightpermanent dead link  net loss attributable to clearwire corporation is  which represents the net loss less noncontrolling interests in net loss of consolidated subsidiaries of  per q and yearend  earnings results  dead link  clearwire inc fundinguniversecom fundinguniverse retrieved    a b softbank to buy  percent stake in sprint sources cnbc retrieved october     sprint and softbank announce completion of merger  sprint newsroom newsroomsprintcom retrieved august     a b jeff bounds april   fixed wireless playtelecom billionaire craig mccaw snaps up clearwire holdings eyes itfs space retrieved    mccaw places new bet on faster cheaper access clearwire to launch cellular internet service the washington post june     whats news   clearwire reports first quarter  results archived march   at the wayback machine  intel motorola put up  million to save wimax fortune cnn july   retrieved    clearwire secures m in financing motorola media center july   archived from the original on  retrieved    clearwiresprint nextel partnership clearwire corp retrieved    clearwire q report clearwir