 company on july   sprint nextel completed acquiring the remaining shares it didnt already own becoming sole owner of clearwire corporation the day after on july   sprint nextel and softbank corp announced the completion of their merger where softbank invested  billion in sprint clearwire provided services to  markets in the united states covering  million potential subscribers sprint corporation owns rights to radio frequency spectrum in the  ghz range which provides service primarily using the g e mobile wimax standard clearwire also provides service to customers in  us cities using the motorola expedience d radio interface which the company refers to as preg clearwire was ranked as the fifth largest wireless provider in the us prior to being acquired with roughly  million subscribers who used the wimax network as of january  sprint ceased operations of the clearwire network on november   contents  history  complete acquisition by sprint nextel  networks  expedience ofdm  preg  wimax e  g  retail products and services  g mobile and fixed wireless  expedience fixed wireless  voip  wholesale products and services  criticism  see also  references  external links historyedit clearwire traces its roots to  when sierra technologies inc spun off certain assets to form a new company clearwire inc based in arlington texas clearwire technologies was formed by a number of investors including sierra ceo jim gero and edward rusty rose a former comanaging partner of the texas rangers clearwire technologies raised about us million from goldman sachs in conjunction with another client who held licenses for spectrum allocated to various educational institutions the former instructional television fixed service itfs band now known as ebs or educational broadband service after goldman provided the funds—which were supposed to be used to roll out the system in key markets across the us—they used a provision of the agreement to take control of the company hiring a new ceo leo j cyr who ousted the entire management team including clearwire ceo brian nerney while diluting the strength of the founders still on the board of directors a holding company controlled by craig mccaw flux llc acquired clearwire incs then parent company clearwire holdings in march  after assuming control mccaw installed executives from mccaw cellular in the key leadership positions at clearwire corp on june   mccaw purchased clearwire inc for an undisclosed amount and used its name and resources as well as technology developed by another mccawowned company nextnet wireless inc to launch his latest effort on october   intel corp teamed up with mccaw to develop and deploy a technology for portable wireless internet access the partnership included an investment by clearwire corp on march   bell canada invested  million us in seattlebased clearwire corpcitation needed clearwire grew from  customers in september  to more than  customers by may  clearwire claimed in september  that  of its markets had more than  penetration of households coveredcitation needed clearwire took a  million infusion of capital from intel and motorola in july  shortly after pulling its initial public offering clearwires equipment manufacturer nextnet wireless was sold to motorola as part of the exchange this investment by these two industry giants had been reported as an attempt to accelerate the development and deployment of wimax networks worldwide an unspecified source claims that att sold clearwire a slice of  ghz spectrum for about  million the spectrum covers markets in the southeast of the us and was formerly owned by bellsouth the spectrum solidifies clearwires position as the second largest holder of  ghz spectrum after sprint nextel att had to sell the spectrum as a condition of its merger with bellsouthcitation needed clearwire and sprint nextel announced a partnership in july  to accelerate deployment of wimax technology across the us the deal was to include a swap of spectrum and markets between the two companies as well as providing roaming capabilities for customers traveling between the companies networks the partnership was terminated at the end of  in  sprints new ceo dan hesse started serious discussions about forming a joint venture between the two companies in the hopes of bringing in outside funding from google intel and best buy on march   an anonymous source stated that sprint and clearwire may get as much as  billion from comcast and  million from time warner cable in financial backing clearwire filed for its initial public offering with the securities and exchange commission in may  the companys underwriters included merrill lynch morgan stanley and jpmorgan chase trading began march   under the ticker symbol clwr on the nasdaq clearwire offered  million shares at  a share and raised approximately us million before the sprint merger craig mccaw was the largest shareholder of the company with a majority of the shares on may   clearwire and sprint nextels wireless broadband unit xohm announced their intent to merge combining sprints g wimax network xohm with clearwires existing prewimax broadband network sprint owns  of the firm with exclearwire shareholders owning  — a consortium of comcast time warner cable intel google and bright house networks invested  billion and own the balance clearwire and the cable companies will buy g mobile broadband from sprint as mvnoscitation needed clearwiresprint nextel officially launched portland oregon as the first market using the new service clearwires g service was branded as clear except in those markets where the clearwire name has already been established and where clear service is not available clear g was available in  of the top  msas in the country covering  million people on march   clearwire named bill morrow as ceo succeeding benjamin wolff who became cochairman with craig mccaw morrow  stepped down as ceo of pacific gas  electric company morrow had previously held a number of senior positi